5thly, At the Beginning of every Line in Poetry; as,


Improve your Time: Time passeth quickly on;

Nor doth so good succeed, as that that's gone.

It is as proper to know how to Subscribe; 
                     •
                  nd how to Direct, as it is how to write a Letter.

